Key Match Events: The game went into extra innings with the Dodgers tying the score in the 8th inning and winning in the 9th with a sacrifice fly.
Aaron Judge doubled to left in the 8th inning, setting up the winning play.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played at Yankee Stadium with a attendance of 49,263.
Others: Umpires included Mark Ripperger, Todd Tichenor, Carlos Torres, Andy Fletcher, Mark Carlson, and Doug Eddings.
